The paper discusses the use of visualization methods to analyze scientific excellence in different regions of the world using Scopus and Web of Science data. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories related to data analysis and visualization. 

cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the use of computer programs to analyze scientific data. 

cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as the paper discusses the identification of high-quality papers based on citation data. 

cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) could be another possible category as the paper discusses the analysis of scientific excellence in different regions of the world. 

cs.CY (Computers and Society) could be a relevant category as the paper discusses the use of geographic information systems to produce density maps. 

cs.SD (Software Engineering) could also be a possible category as the paper discusses the use of computer programs to analyze scientific data.
